        <link>http://www.ietf.org/internet-drafts/draft-templin-dtn-ltpfrag-06.txt</link>
        <title>"LTP Fragmentation", Fred Templin</title>
        <dc:date>2021-11-19T23:00:00-00:00</dc:date>
        <description>The Licklider Transmission Protocol (LTP) provides a reliable datagram convergence layer for the Delay/Disruption Tolerant Networking (DTN) Bundle Protocol.  In common practice, LTP is often configured over UDP/IP sockets and inherits its maximum segment size from the maximum-sized UDP/IP datagram, however when this size exceeds the maximum IP packet size for the path a service known as IP fragmentation must be employed.  This document discusses LTP interactions with IP fragmentation and mitigations for managing the amount of IP fragmentation employed.</description>
    </item>
